#Load graphics packages & stats packages needed
source("R/libraries.R")
#Plots used for QK use the ggplot classic theme, with some tweaks. Tweaks are consolidated into theme_QK; use this theme for figures and tweak the theme to avoid repetitive code changes. Also uses variables for axis, fill, line colours, etc.
source("R/appearance.R")

Fig 12.1

steiger <- read.csv("data/steiger.csv")
steiger$ltime <- log10(steiger$time)
library(dplyr)
steiger$matingnumber<-fct_recode(steiger$matingnumber, "1st"= "first", "2nd"="second","3rd"="third", "4th"="fourth", "5th"="fifth")
steiger_sum <- summarySE(steiger, measurevar= 'ltime', groupvars= 'matingnumber')
f12_1<-ggplot(steiger_sum, aes(x=matingnumber, y=ltime))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width=.6, fill=lf,color=lc) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=ltime-se, ymax=ltime+se), width=0) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0)) +
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("1st","2nd","3rd", "4th", "5th"))+
    labs(x = "Mating number", y = "Log (Time)")+       #Omits x axis label, as bar labels sufficient
    theme_qk()+
    theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(colour = "black", size=8),    
    legend.position = "top",
  legend.title = element_blank(),
  legend.text=element_text(size=9),
  )
f12_1

Fig 12.2

chadha <- read.csv("data/chadha.csv")
chadha1 <- subset(chadha, treat=="100WHC")
chadha1$plant<-as.factor(chadha1$plant)
f12_2<-ggplot(chadha1, aes(x = week, y = noleaves, group=plant, color=plant)) +
  geom_line()+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(2,4,6,8))+
  labs(x = "Week", y = "No. leaves")+
    theme_qk()+
    theme(
    legend.position = "none",
   )+
  scale_colour_uchicago()
f12_2

** Version with slopes rather than data points

chadha <- read.csv("data/chadha.csv")
chadha1 <- subset(chadha, treat=="100WHC")
chadha1$plant<-as.factor(chadha1$plant)
f12_2a<-ggplot(chadha1, aes(x = week, y = noleaves, group=plant, colour=plant)) +
  geom_smooth(se=FALSE,method="lm")+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(2,4,6,8))+
  labs(x = "Week", y = "No. leaves")+
    theme_qk()+
    theme(
    legend.position = "none",
   )+
  scale_colour_uchicago()

Figure 12.4

garcia <- read.csv("data/garcia.csv")
garcia$toad <- factor(garcia$toad)
garcia$timefac <- factor(garcia$time, ordered=TRUE)
garcia2.aov <- aov(cumattack~treatment*timefac+Error(toad), garcia)
emm1<-emmeans(garcia2.aov, ~treatment|timefac)      #extract means
Note: re-fitting model with sum-to-zero contrasts
emm2<-as.data.frame(emm1)                    #convert data table to frame

f12_4<-ggplot(emm2,aes(x=timefac,y=emmean,shape=treatment, group=treatment, color=treatment))+
  geom_point(position=pd, size=3,show.legend = FALSE)+    #size=3 for larger symbols, as means shown (so fewer points on fig)
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = emmean-SE, ymax = emmean+SE), width=0, position = pd,show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_line(aes(colour=treatment), position=pd, size=ls)+
 scale_color_uchicago()+
  scale_linetype_manual(labels = c("Control", "Experimental"))+
  labs(x = "Time (min)", y = "Cumulative attacks"
       )+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(color="black",size=8),
    legend.position = c(.4,.85),
    legend.justification = c("right", "top"),
    legend.box.just = "right",
    legend.title = element_blank(),
)

skrip <- read.csv("data/skrip.csv")
skrip_stats <- summarySE(skrip,measurevar='wmass', groupvars= c('diet','exercise','order'), na.rm=TRUE)
pd=position_dodge(width=0.0)
f12_5<-ggplot(skrip_stats,aes(x=order, y=wmass,color=exercise, linetype=diet))+
#  geom_point(position=pd, size=3)+
  geom_line(size=ls)+
scale_color_uchicago(name="Exercise",labels=c("Exercise", "No exercise"))+
scale_linetype_manual(name="Diet",values=c("solid", "dashed"), labels = c("Control", "Supplemented"))+
#scale_shape_discrete(name="Diet", labels = c("Control", "Supplemented"))+
  labs(x = "Mating order", y = "Fresh egg mass (g)") +
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    legend.text = element_text(size=7),
    legend.title= element_text(size=8)
  )

Figure 12.6

parkinson <- read.csv("data/park2002.csv")
parkinson$labund<-log10(parkinson$abund)
park_stats <- summarySE(parkinson,measurevar='labund', groupvars= c('habitat','month','ampm'))
#Separate interaction plots for am and pm
park_stats$monthn<-fct_recode(park_stats$month,'1'="nov",'2'= "dec",'3'="jan",'4'="feb")
park_stats$monthn<-as.numeric(park_stats$monthn)
xl=c("Nov", "Dec", "Jan", "Feb")
emm3<-filter(park_stats, ampm=="am")
p1<-ggplot(emm3,aes(x=monthn,y=labund, color=habitat))+
    geom_line(size=ls)+
#scale_color_uchicago(labels = c("Permanent", "Temporary","Non-wetland"))+
  labs(x = NULL, y = "log Abundance", title="am"
       )+
    ylim(0.5,2)+
    scale_x_continuous(labels=xl)+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(color="black"),
    legend.title=element_blank()
)
emm3<-filter(park_stats, ampm=="pm")
p2<-ggplot(emm3,aes(x=monthn,y=labund, color=habitat))+
    geom_line(size=ls)+
#scale_color_grey(start=0.2, end=0.8, labels = c("Permanent", "Temporary","Non-wetland"))+
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, title="pm"
       )+
    ylim(0.5,2)+
    scale_x_continuous(labels=xl)+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(color="black"),
    legend.title=element_blank()
)
f12_6<-p1+p2+plot_layout(guides="collect")&scale_color_uchicago(labels = c("Permanent", "Temporary","Non-wetland")) 
f12_6
